The paper deals with learning the rationality of agents in games, which is a core problem in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep learning framework for end-to-end learning, which falls under cs.LG. The paper deals with zero-sum games, which is a subfield of game theory, and hence cs.GT is also a likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an efficient first-order primal-dual method, which is a technique used in optimization, and hence cs.DS and cs.SY are also likely sub-categories.
